==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outing
<hw>Out"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of going out;
an airing; an excursion; <as>as, a summer
<ex>outing</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A feast given by an apprentice when he is out of his
time.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outjest</ent>⟦br⟧
